HEADWORD: Misbegotten
<hw>Mis`be*got"ten</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>p. a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Unlawfully or
irregularly begotten; of bad or disreputable origin; pernicious.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Valor <xex>misbegot</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Poorly designed or planned; badly carried out;
ill-conceived.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misbehave</ent>⟦br⟧
